Text.SourceString: Hello… <PlayerName>$player</>, isn’t it?//It’s nice to see more people choosing to work with their hands.//It’s very rare in this day and age.

Yes, I own the general store, but nobody’s buying anything lately.//I had to scale down…a lot. Look at it! The store is pretty much dead.//<portrait=annoyed>That oil spill last year <Italic>really</> kicked us in the butt.
Hello… <PlayerName>$player</>, isn’t it?//It’s nice to see more people choosing to work with their hands.//It’s very rare in this day and age.

Yes, I own the general store, but nobody’s buying anything lately.//I had to scale down…a lot. The store is pretty much dead.//<portrait=annoyed>That oil spill last year <Italic>really</> kicked us in the butt.
We have profit sharing here.//On top of her salary, <NPCName>Eva</> gets part of the profit from the baked goods sales.
Of course I am. I’m very proud of our system.//It won’t work for every business, but we’re pretty small here. I think it’s working all right so far.
Do you need anything? I’m usually open from nine to five.
I wish more people would take up farming. The soil here is so fertile.//We can grow literally anything. If you ask me, I think people are too comfortable to do work that requires labor…
Of course, I would do it. But if I start farming, who would do this?
Working hard, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It’s nice to see I’m not the only one working hard around here… A foreign concept to some people.
I only sell seeds for a specific season.//So if you want to grow sugarcane in the Fall, you’ll need to save the seeds yourself.
I don’t see it as a problem. Don’t you have a chest?//I haven’t met a farmer without one, so I assume you do.
The weather forecast is never 100 percent correct, but it’s still worth paying attention to.
It’s still somewhat accurate, no?
I like the smell of the ocean.//It’s fresh and a little salty.
I get some of my supplies from neighboring islands.//And from you, of course.
<NPCName>Luke</>? Oh, no. He sells electronics. Are we talking about the same <NPCName>Luke</>?//I get my items delivered here by boat or through <NPCName>Ben</>. He’s rather cheap.

You can watch television every day. The content usually changes daily… Usually.
No need to be overly impressed, <PlayerName>$player</>.//That is indeed how television works.
Puzzles are good for the mind. It’s a mental exercise to keep your brain sharp.
Why, of course. Every other day, no skipping for me. We need to keep our brains sharp.//It’s a muscle that needs exercise like any other.
If you pay attention, they broadcast general information about Coral Island on the local network sometimes.
You do have a television, don’t you?
I sell bread and cookies.//Not just seeds, <PlayerName>$player</>
Oh, no, no. I don’t. If that worries you, rest assured I don’t go anywhere near the oven. Heh, heh! <NPCName>Eva</> does the baking.//She’s a good baker.
The islanders like the Tavern. It's called Fishensips now...it used to be the Tavern, back in the day when their dad ran it.//People go there on weekend nights especially, if you want to catch them.
Why, yes. I might be there too. Dancing, maybe.
I purposely took a day off today. I want to spend the day with people who are important to me.
Relaxing and whatnot.
Sunny sells fresh seafood here and there. It depends on what he gets from <NPCName>Theo</>.//It isn’t always good.
The store is closed today. If you need anything, stop by tomorrow.
I took a day off yesterday. I wanted to spend the day playing chess.//<portrait=unimpressed>Relaxing and whatnot.

<NPCName>Ling</> can help you upgrade your crops by upgrading the quality of the seeds.
I heard she can also upgrade your animal feed!

Ready for the new week?
The store is especially busy on the first Monday of every season.
How’s my tie? It got crooked earlier while I was shelving some flour.
How can I be presentable if my tie isn’t straight? Disaster!
Oh, you cleaned up a bit, didn’t you?//You look nice! Presentable and very respectable.
I always say to the youngsters, one must look the part to play the part.
It is <Italic>indeed</> Thursday.//Is something the matter?

Oops! Errr… No, it’s Sunday. It isn’t Thursday.
I’m not too worried about the folks at Pufferfish.//When they move in here and see how we’re home to exotic fish, I hope it changes their mind.
But of course, the island would need to improve first, and in the meantime, I would hope nobody’s selling their property to them.
It’s not a bad idea to keep some seeds on hand so you can get a head start next year!
Are you listening to my advice? This is all-important. You will understand soon enough.//<portrait=unimpressed>Youth.

The cherry trees near the lake are blooming again. Which means it’s the time of the year when we gather around the lake and barbeque.
I think <NPCName>Emily</> and I are bringing fresh chards to the festival… Yes. Some chards!//That’ll be good.
There’s still time to start planting, <PlayerName>$player</>. Just make sure to read the description to find out the lifespan of the plant.
Trees take about four weeks to grow. It’s longer than other plants, but the good thing is you don’t need to water them all that much.
They’re self-sufficient, you see.
I think it’s time for another haircut. My hair is getting so long.//My oh my!
You can’t tell?//Are you being polite? *sighs*

It’s probably not pleasant to be right by the oven so early in the morning in this kind of weather.
But that’s life. Sometimes you just have to do what you have to do and get on with it.
It’s probably not the most pleasant work to be by the oven in this kind of heat.
But that’s life. Sometimes you just have to do what you have to do and get on with it.
This must be a pretty busy season for you, huh?
Nonsense. If it isn’t your busy season, then you must make it so.//<portrait=normal>It’s Summer, <PlayerName>$player</>!
There’s still time to start planting, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Just make sure to read the description to find out the plant’s growth cycle.
It’s not a bad idea to keep some seeds on hand so you can get a head start next year!
Are you listening to my advice? This is all-important.//You will understand soon enough.
Summer vegetables are crunchy and vibrant.//They’re the best for the assorted grilled platter.
Summer vegetables are crunchy and vibrant.//They’re the best for the assorted grilled platter.
People have complained about the store being too cold, but unfortunately, I have to keep the cooler on to ensure the produce stays fresh.
So the store is always a bit chilly in the Fall.//Can’t do anything about it.

Though I’m not sure when he’ll be back from his Fall shenanigans.//You’re on your own with that.

They’re self-sufficient, you see.
It’s going to be a slow Winter… I can already tell.
The first week in, and I’m already ready for Spring… *sighs*
My wife’s birthday is coming up, and I’m not sure what to get her.
<NPCName>Emily</> loves artisan oils. So once, I thought I’d give her the oil we had in at the store at the time. Gosh, was I wrong!//She hated it.
I offered to close the store and spend the day with <NPCName>Emily</> tomorrow, but she insisted otherwise. So I think we’ll just have a quiet birthday dinner at home.
No, no, no. Not my birthday.//It’s for her birthday.
People have complained about the store being too cold, but unfortunately, I have to keep the cooler on to ensure the produce stays fresh.
The store is always a bit unbearable in the Winter.//Can’t do anything about it.

If you’re looking to farm this Winter, your best bet is <NPCName>Ben</>.//He may have more Winter seeds after his Fall shenanigans.
Still got a lot of errands to run, <PlayerName>$player</>?
It’s important for me to visit these folks often to make sure I can still beat them at chess.
HEY, <NPCName>JIM</>! Did you hear that? Ha ha!
Thankfully, it didn’t storm, huh?
So you tell me, <PlayerName>$player</>. As a farmer, how do you deal with this weather?
I used to be the dancer in the friend group. Can you tell?
I can’t dance as much as I used to. With work and daily responsibilities, there’s less time to practice.
Yum… Delicious.
It’s nice to go out every once in a while, even if it’s raining like this.
Fortunately for us, this place is close to the house, so we don’t have to walk too far in the rain.
Excuse me, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m trying to get my wife home before we get soaked.
It would’ve felt so much colder in here if we hadn’t been dancing earlier.
The thunder has been nonstop like this since I woke up!
Still got a lot of errands to run?
I suggest you wait until the storm dies down before you plant anything because it might wreck your farm.
It’s nice to go out every once in a while, even if it’s raining like this.
Fortunately for us, this place is close by, so we don’t have to walk too far in the rain.
Excuse me, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m trying to get my wife home before we get soaked.
There aren’t many vegetables that can survive Winter here, so I don’t carry that many seeds.
If you’re looking to farm this Winter, your best bet is <NPCName>Ben</>.//He may have more Winter seeds after his Fall shenanigans.
It’s nice to go out every once in a while, even if it’s snowing like this.
Fortunately for us, this place is close to the house, so we don’t have to walk too far in this freezing weather.
Excuse me, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m trying to get my wife home before we freeze to death.
Some green tea would be lovely, wouldn’t it?
Hello, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s great to see you here. Looking for the most profitable seeds?
I suggest you plant what you want, and the rest will follow.
Welcome! Are you shopping?
That’s the best price I can give you. Take it or leave it.
How can I help you today?
I don’t see the need to do discounts, since I always price my items as low as I possibly can.
Now, keep in mind I only sell the best quality items, <PlayerName>$player</>. At this price, they’re basically free!
Certain people complained that I don’t do rebates. That is false! I do, in fact, do rebates.//But only for select customers who purchase over a specific amount.
It’s probably a good thing it’s not more well known.//I’d hate to have to deal with more people complaining about it.
<PlayerName>$player</>, you look like you’d be a good chess player. We must have a game one of these nights.
Not tonight. Tonight is no good… I’m finishing up a puzzle, and I need full concentration.
In good time…
Oh, it’s a bit odd having you here so late. It’s definitely not something I’m used to yet.
<PlayerName>$player</>! Have you had dinner?
It’s nice of you to visit! One of these nights, I must challenge you to a game of chess.
Not tonight. Tonight is no good… My show is on.
It’s important for me to beat these folks at chess every week. Ha ha! To make sure they know who’s actually the best!
HEY <NPCName>JIM</>! Did you hear that? Hah hah!
I always enjoy the walk here.
The Tavern is one of the oldest buildings on this island. Aside from the mansion, that is.//It’s been refurbished many times, so you probably can’t tell.
